CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 25, 1955, pg. 28, reads: "Masons Bury Ex-Postal Superintendent - The remains of George Gould, Masonic leader, and former superintendent of Wylie Avenue Post Office Station, were transported from Bethesda Presbyterian Church by Masonic pallbearers Tuesday following funeral services there. He died Saturday. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Women and men walking out of Bethesda Presbyterian Church, including two men wearing dark suits leading woman wearing dark suit, for funeral of George Gould
